				<p><p>As @acs said, PID control is used for individual joint control.  And you ignore all non-linearities.  And typically this is good enough.  Sure each joint's control isn't completely optimal, but they should be stable.  You can have each joint doing position or velocity control.  Then you can do trajectory control at a higher level.</p>

<p>For whole arm control where you want to take into account non-linearities, you do non-linear control.  <a href="https://github.com/RobotLocomotion/drake/wiki" rel="nofollow">Drake</a> is one such toolbox that does this.</p>
</p><br>
